A 22-year-old businessman was shot dead at his shop in Lethabong near Rustenburg, North West police said on Saturday. Sergeant Kelebogile Moleko said an anonymous woman called Lethabong police reporting that a person was shot dead on Thursday night. The police found the man lying face up and bleeding from the head. It appears he was shot in the head. The shop was intact and appeared as if nothing was taken [from the shop], she said. -African News Agency (ANA) For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter. For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.